docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Three months before anyone starts voting in the Democratic primaries, advisers for Bernie Sanders are confident about the new voters they are registering in Iowa. They expect a decisive victory in New Hampshire, where Mr. Sanders, the senator from neighboring Vermont, is seen as a local. And in California, a state the campaign views as clearing a path to the nomination, they believe Mr. Sanders has a clear advantage with the not-so-secret weapon of Latino voters.
